{"word":"παράλιος","slug":"παράλιος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>παράλιος</b></el> <el>(παρ-άλιος, η, ον) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>= <a href='S:πάραλος'><el>πάραλος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>by the sea</i>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><el>ἡ</el> (<a href='S:scilicet'>sc.</a> <el>γῆ</el> or <el>χώρα</el>) <i>the seacoast, sea-board</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristotle'>Arist.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>the eastern coast of Attica</i>, between Hymettus and the sea, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}